{"_id":"3nxTkqxcKVAumSxd","name":"Hindered","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"The character’s movement is hindered, slowing them. The character cannot attempt any movement as a Free Action. Further, the character may only move to within Close range as a Minor Action move, and only to within Medium range as a Standard Action move. Finally, the Difficulty of all terrain tests is increased by one step for the character."},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/rule.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NCmEISUTHJPgQdQD","name":"Deaf","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"The character’s hearing has been severely damaged. Upon being deafened, a character suffers 3§ mental damage, and any skill test reliant on hearing (normally Observation, Insight, Command, Persuade, etc.) increases in Difficulty by two steps."},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/rule.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"UOC9g5q4t5j58rWT","name":"Blind","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"The character’s vision is severely damaged. Upon being blinded, a character suffers 3§ mental damage, and any skill test reliant on vision (normally Observation, Insight, Ranged Weapons, Sailing, etc.) increases in Difficulty by two steps."},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/rule.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"V5jk5GpRC0fqEdKY","name":"Poisoned","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"The character’s body suffers the effects of some form of vile toxin. While each poison has a specific effect, the general effect is to grant the character the Staggered condition."},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/poison.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YxXXg6h11jRAnOig","name":"Burning X","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"The target is set on fire. This condition lasts for a number of rounds equal to the number of Effects rolled on the attack that inflicted it. If no § were rolled, the cause of the burning effect will list a duration. At the end of the target’s turn, the target suffers X§ physical and mental damage (roll once and apply it to both), ignoring Armor Soak. Any physical damage caused by Burning X has the Incendiary attack Quality, and Effects rolled increase the number of rounds that the character remains aflame. A character may attempt a Clear Minor Action to remove this effect, while a prone character can spend a Standard Action rolling around, extinguishing the flames. The latter works as a Clear Action but reduces the Difficulty by two steps. If the character is hit by another Burning attack or effect while already ablaze, the existing status is extended by a number of rounds equal to the number of Effects rolled.burning.png"},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/rule.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gp6UK93HenxH8l0u","name":"Staggered","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"A Staggered character can only perform a Standard Action in a turn if the player is willing to pay 1 point of Doom. A Staggered character cannot perform a Reaction unless spending 1 Fortune point in addition to the reaction’s normal Doom cost."},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/rule.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"rRLhDR0umqI4MWNU","name":"Dazed","permission":{"default":0},"type":"rule","data":{"description":"All skill tests performed by a Dazed character increase in Difficulty by one step until the Dazed condition ends."},"img":"systems/conan2d20/asset/image/rule.png","effects":[]}
